message.content:
The provided bytecode is machine language for the EVM (Ethereum Virtual Machine). It's extremely difficult, almost impossible, to reverse-engineer it back to the original Solidity source code, especially without any additional information about the contract's functionality.

Bytecode is the compiled version of Solidity code which is deployed to the Ethereum blockchain. It is not meant to be human-readable, and reverse-engineering it would be a complex task, if possible at all.

If you have the original Solidity code, I would be able to help you understand it, debug it, or modify it. However, from the bytecode alone, I can't provide the Solidity code.
